Migrating from udev 216 to eudev 1.10-r2 (March 2015) is straigthforward : http://forums.gentoo.org/viewtopic-p-7712064.html#7712064

emerge --ask eudev

The network interface naming convention is not the same so you'll need to re-link /etc/init.d from net.lo to net.eth0 or whatever networkin interface you use and add net.eth0 to the default runlevel

ln -s /etc/init.d/net.lo /etc/init.d/net.eth0

then you conf.d :

ln -s /etc/conf.d/net.lo /etc/conf.d/net.eth0

Add to the default runlevel :

rc-update add net.eth0 default

